{"parse":{"title":"Controversia","pageid":37339205,"revid":781555942,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For the album, see <a href=\"/wiki/Controversia_(album)\" title=\"Controversia (album)\">Controversia (album)</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4b/Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG/220px-Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4b/Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG/330px-Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4b/Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG/440px-Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"893\" data-file-height=\"813\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Seneka_Starszy_Sevilla_cropped.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/Seneca_the_Elder\" title=\"Seneca the Elder\">Seneca the Elder</a> compiled a study of the classic themes in his ten volumes of <i>Controversi\u00e6</i>.</div></div></div>\n<p>A <i><b>controversia</b></i> is an exercise in <a href=\"/wiki/Rhetoric\" title=\"Rhetoric\">rhetoric</a>; a form of <a href=\"/wiki/Declamation\" title=\"Declamation\">declamation</a> in which the student speaks for one side in a notional legal case such as treason or poisoning.  The facts of the matter and relevant law are presented in a persuasive manner, in the style of a legal counsel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Controversia&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The exercise was used in <a href=\"/wiki/Ancient_Rome\" title=\"Ancient Rome\">ancient Rome</a>, where it was, with the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Suasoria\" title=\"Suasoria\">suasoria</a></i>, the final stage of a course in rhetoric at an <a href=\"/wiki/Academy\" title=\"Academy\">academy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  <a href=\"/wiki/Seneca_the_Elder\" title=\"Seneca the Elder\">Seneca the Elder</a> was an expert rhetorician and, from memory, compiled a set of classical themes for this exercise: the <i>Controversi\u00e6</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Controversia&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFHeinrich_Lausberg,_translated_by_David_E._Orton1998\" class=\"citation\">Heinrich Lausberg, translated by David E. Orton (1998), <i>Handbook of Literary Rhetoric</i>, BRILL, pp.&#160;500\u2013501, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9789004107052\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9789004107052\">9789004107052</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Handbook+of+Literary+Rhetoric&amp;rft.pages=500-501&amp;rft.pub=BRILL&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=9789004107052&amp;rft.au=Heinrich+Lausberg%2C+translated+by+David+E.+Orton&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AControversia\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Susanna Morton Braund (1997). \"Declamation and contestation in satire\". <i>Roman Eloquence: Rhetoric in Society and Literature</i>. Routledge. p.&#160;148. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780415125444\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780415125444\">9780415125444</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Declamation+and+contestation+in+satire&amp;rft.btitle=Roman+Eloquence%3A+Rhetoric+in+Society+and+Literature&amp;rft.pages=148&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.isbn=9780415125444&amp;rft.au=Susanna+Morton+Braund&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AControversia\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><i>The Oxford Encyclopedia of Ancient Greece and Rome</i>, <b>1</b>, <a href=\"/wiki/Oxford_University_Press\" title=\"Oxford University Press\">Oxford University Press</a>, 2010, p.&#160;276, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780195170726\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780195170726\">9780195170726</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp